## Installing more
- Python: `uv add <pkg>` (in a project) or `uvx <tool>` for one-offs — never global `pip`
- Node: `pnpm add <pkg>`; `npm i -g <tool>` for CLIs
{% if install_rust %}- Rust: `cargo install <tool>`
{% endif %}- System: `sudo apt-get install -y <pkg>` (last resort)


# Working style
- Ask when something is unclear instead of guessing — discuss and pick the best option.
- Close the loop: verify your work, use an oracle (run it, test it) whenever you can.
- Run the available linters and tests on anything you touched before calling a task done.
- Experiment freely — this is a throwaway box. Restart things, recreate the db, try stuff out.
- Don't commit or open/comment on PRs; leave that to the operator. After a task, hand back a clear, concise commit message.
